main event: Multiple witnesses observed a bright object in the sky on June 3, 1961, which was tracked by radar.
interesting points: The object was observed as a source of aircraft lights on a 100-degree course., The object was tracked on ground radar at around 30,000 ft., Witnesses described the object as slightly oval-shaped with extremely bright lights., The radar station reported a target moving up and down at an altitude of 34,400 feet., Pilots scrambled to intercept but could not visually recognize the object due to electronic countermeasure interference.
sighted object: a bright oval-shaped object emitting bright lights
witness description: civilian witnesses and personnel from the 663rd Radar Station
